214	+// E_PARSE_ERROR or E_PARSE_TIMEOUT depending on ParseStatus.Code), reusing
215	+// its code, severity, and detail so the wording lines up across both paths.
216	+// The effect wording is dependents-specific: entities the parser still
217	+// recovers keep counting exactly as before -- this warning is purely
218	+// additive observability, not a change to which entities get counted.
219	+func dependentsParseFailureWarning(path string, status ParseStatus) ProviderWarning {
